title: Brian Kemp - Wikipedia
snippet: Brian Porter Kemp (born November 2, 1963) is an American politician serving as the 83rd governor of Georgia since 2019. A member of the Republican Party, Kemp served as the state's 27th Secretary of State from 2010 to 2018, and as a member of the Georgia State Senate from 2003 to 2007.

title: Republican Gov. Brian Kemp endorsed by Democratic predecessor
snippet: On Wednesday, Gov. Brian Kemp’s re-election campaign announced the endorsement of Joe Frank Harris, who served as Georgia’s chief executive from 1983 to 1991.
